items.name: Chateau de la Roche Courbon
items.description: Chateau de la Roche Courbon in Charente-Maritime department of France.

items.name: Temple of Hadrian in Ephesus Ancient City
items.description: The famous temple was built before 138 A.D. for Emperor Hadrian’s visit.

items.name: Amazing beach Navagio in Zakynthos, Greece
Arles, France
items.description: The ancient Roman Arena, a 1st-century amphitheater is one of the best preserved of antiquity.

items.name: Scenic view in Phuket, Thailand
items.description: Scenic Phuket landscape, paradisiacal and idyllic beach.

items.name: Lighthouse
items.description: Did you know that a lighthouse is like a traffic sign on the sea? The two main purposes of a lighthouse are to serve as a navigational aid and to warn boats of dangerous areas.

items.name: Dubai Skyline at Night, UAE
items.description: Wow view of Dubai skyline at night.

items.name: Tucson, Arizona
items.description: Famous for its dramatic beauty, the Sonoran Desert covers Tucson region with spectacular cacti – including the giant saguaro, a symbol of the American Southwest.

items.name: Guilin, China
items.description: Beautiful landscape of Guilin, Li River and Karst mountains. It is located near Yangshuo County, Guilin City, Guangxi Province, China.

items.name: Zhangjiajie National Forest Park, Hunan, China
items.description: After being declared a UNESCO World Heritage Site and a UNESCO Global Geopark, visitors to Zhangjiajie are guaranteed to find a pristine setting in the park's many scenic areas.

items.name: Torres del Paine National Park, Chile
items.description: Torres del Paine National Park, in Chile’s Patagonia region, is known for its soaring mountains, bright blue icebergs that cleave from glaciers and golden pampas that shelter rare wildlife such as llama-like guanacos.

items.name: View of Mount Cook, New Zealand
items.description: Mount Cook is the highest mountain in New Zealand. Its height, as of 2014, is listed as 3,724 metres.

items.name: Water on field terraced of Mu Cang Chai, Vietnam
items.description: Located just 100km south of the Chinese border, Mu Cang Chai can be reached via a winding road northwest from the capital, Hanoi, and is situated 1,000m above sea level.

items.name: Phi-Phi island, Krabi Province, Thailand
items.description: The Phi Phi Islands are an island group in Thailand, between the large island of Phuket and the Straits of Malacca coast of Thailand. The islands are administratively part of Krabi Province.

items.name: Batman Mount, Iceland
items.description: The region is very dramatic and a wonderful place to visit.

items.name: Lake Altausseer See, Austria
items.description: Altaussee is a municipality and spa town in the district of Liezen in Styria, Austria. The small village is nestled on the shores of the Lake Altaussee, beneath the Loser Plateau. Occupying an area of 92 km², Altaussee is home to 1,777 people.

items.name: Porto Katsiki in Lefkada, Greece
items.description: Porto Katsiki is a beach on the Ionian island of Lefkada, Greece. The name is said to be because formerly only goats could reach this area.

items.name: Stonehenge, England, UK
items.description: Stonehenge is a prehistoric monument in Wiltshire, England. It consists of a ring of standing stones, each around 4.0 m high, 2.1 m wide, and weighing around 25 tons. The stones are set within earthworks in the middle of the most dense complex of Neolithic and Bronze Age monuments in England.

items.name: Dubai skyline, UAE
items.description: Dubai, the largest city in the United Arab Emirates, is home to many modern high-rises, 108 of which stand taller than 180 metres.

items.name: Rice fields in Mu Cang Chai, YenBai, Vietnam
items.description: Mù Cang Chải is a district of Yen Bai province. Mù Cang Chải Rice Terrace has been recognized as one of the unique landscapes of Vietnam, it was at the highest ranked national landscape in 2007.

items.name: Communication Palace, Madrid
items.description: Cibeles Palace, formally known as Palacio de Comunicaciones, is a complex composed of two buildings with white facades and is located in one of the historical centres of Madrid, Spain.

items.name: Brussels City Hall
items.description: The Town Hall of the City of Brussels is a Gothic building from the Middle Ages. It is located on the famous Grand Place in Brussels, Belgium, opposite the Brussels City Museum.

items.name: Lake Pukaki, New Zealand
items.description: Lake Pukaki is the largest of three roughly parallel alpine lakes running north–south along the northern edge of the Mackenzie Basin on New Zealand's South Island.

items.name: Horses on Easter Island
items.description: Easter Island, a Chilean territory, is a remote volcanic island in Polynesia. Its native name is Rapa Nui. It’s famed for archaeological sites, including nearly 900 monumental statues called moai, created by inhabitants during the 13th–16th centuries.

items.name: Ad Deir, Petra
items.description: Ad Deir, is a monumental building carved out of rock in the ancient Jordanian city of Petra. Arguably one of the most iconic monuments in the Petra Archaeological Park, the Monastery is located high in the hills northwest of the Petra city center.

items.name: Falzarego pass, Italy
items.description: The Falzarego Pass is a high mountain pass in the province of Belluno in Italy. It mainly connects the territory of Agordo and Cortina d'Ampezzo.

items.name: Close up of impressive golden eagle
items.description: The golden eagle is one of the best-known birds of prey in the Northern Hemisphere. It is the most widely distributed species of eagle. Golden eagles use their agility and speed combined with powerful feet and massive, sharp talons to snatch up a variety of prey, mainly hares, rabbits, and marmots and other ground squirrels.

items.name: Vorontsov Palace, Ukraine
items.description: The Vorontsov Palace is a 19th-century palace and colonnade in Odessa, Ukraine. The present day palace is only the front part of the original structure, the less valuable part of the complex, the Orlov wing was torn down. In the second half of the 20th century, the palace had two fires.

items.name: Famous place Stokksnes Cape, Iceland
items.description: Stokksnes is located south to the mountain Kastarárfjall, where the dent Vestarahorn was featured in the Bollywood film Dilwale.

items.name: Soca river in Bovec, Slovenia
items.description: One of the most beautiful rivers in Europe, the Soča is an important natural treasure in the Triglav National Park. It is famous for its deep emerald colour and brisk rapids in the upstream area.

items.name: Neuschwanstein Castle, Germany
items.description: Neuschwanstein Castle is a 19th-century Romanesque Revival palace on a rugged hill above the village of Hohenschwangau near Füssen in southwest Bavaria, Germany. The palace was commissioned by Ludwig II of Bavaria as a retreat and in honour of Richard Wagner.

items.name: Famous neo-renaissance Peles Castle, Romania
items.description: Peleș Castle is a Neo-Renaissance castle in the Carpathian Mountains, near Sinaia, in Prahova County, Romania, built between 1873 and 1914. Its inauguration was held in 1883. It was constructed for King Carol I.

items.name: Fantastic sunrise over Godafoss waterfall, Iceland
items.description: Goðafoss is a waterfall in northern Iceland. It is located along the country's main ring road at the junction with the Sprengisandur highland road. The water of the river Skjálfandafljót falls from a height of 12 metres over a width of 30 metres.

items.name: The Red Rocks Bay, Sardinia, Italy
items.description: The Red Rocks Bay opens to the east of the Arbatax port, a tourist neighbourhood of Tortolì, with a background of white rocks and tall red granite boulders that give this place a unique and fascinating look.

items.name: Fantastic view on cape Caccia , Italy
items.description: Cape Caccia one of the most amazing wonders of Sardinia. Capo Caccia is located within a protected marine park, and its sheer cliffs are scattered with marine caves, both on the surface or partially/totally submerged. The sea that surrounds the cliffs has the most beautiful and clear waters of the Mediterranean Sea with colors ranging from emerald to turquoise.

items.name: Beautiful Seljalandsfoss waterfall, Iceland
items.description: Seljalandsfoss is a waterfall in Iceland. Seljalandsfoss is located in the South Region in Iceland right by Route 1 and the road that leads to Þórsmörk Road 249. The waterfall drops 60 m and is part of the Seljalands River that has its origin in the volcano glacier Eyjafjallajökull.

items.name: The Cathedral of Curtea de Arges, Romania
items.description: The Cathedral of Curtea de Argeș is a Romanian Orthodox cathedral in Curtea de Argeș, Romania. It is located on the grounds of the Curtea de Argeș Monastery, and is dedicated to Dormition of the Mother of God. The building is the seat of the Archdiocese of Argeș and Muscel.

items.name: Hallstatt mountain village, Austria
items.description: Hallstatt is a small town in the district of Gmunden, in the Austrian state of Upper Austria. Hallstatt is known for its production of salt, dating back to prehistoric times.

items.name: Boiling mud pots in Hverir, Iceland
items.description: Hverir is characterized by boiling mud pots and fumaroles that steam. The area smells like sulfur.

items.name: Coastal town Vieste in Puglia, Italy
items.description: Vieste is a coastal town in Gargano National Park, in southeast Italy. It’s known for its beaches, like Scialara, home to the imposing Pizzomunno limestone monolith, and the broad Spiaggia di San Lorenzo.

items.name: Gosausee mountain lakes, Austria
items.description: Gosauseen are three lakes in the south-western, Alpine part of Upper Austria. They are situated near the town of Gosau, which is close to Salzburg. The mountains that encircle the lakes are called the Dachstein Mountains, whose glaciers partially shaped the landforms and still influence the hydrology of the area.

items.name: Trains through the ghats of Khandala
items.description: Khandala is a hill station in the Western Ghat mountains of Maharashtra, western India. Some of the popular trains traveling to Khandala are Cstm Fast Pass to Mumbai operating 7 times a week.

items.name: Hvitserkur, Iceland
items.description: Hvítserkur is a 15 m high basalt stack along the eastern shore of the Vatnsnes peninsula, in northwest Iceland. The rock has two holes at the base, which give it the appearance of a dragon who is drinking.

items.name: Natural travertine pools, Pamukkale, Turkey
items.description: Pamukkale, meaning "cotton castle" in Turkish, is a natural site in Denizli in southwestern Turkey. Pamukkale is a tourist attraction. It is recognized as a World Heritage Site.

items.name: Laowuchang village, China
items.description: Spectacular rice terrace, called the “air garden”, in front of Laowuchang village, in Yuanjiajie area of Wulingyuan National Park, Zhangjiajie, China. This national park inspired “Avatar” movie.

items.name: Beautiful sunrise in Barcelona seen from Park Guell
items.description: The park was built from 1900 to 1914 and was officially opened as a public park in 1926. In 1984, UNESCO declared the park a World Heritage Site

items.name: Curious sea lion
items.description: Sea lion swimming underwater in tidal lagoon in the Galapagos Islands.

items.name: Petra, Jordan
items.description: Petra is a famous archaeological site in Jordan's southwestern desert. Dating to around 300 B.C., it was the capital of the Nabatean Kingdom. Accessed via a narrow canyon called Al Siq, it contains tombs and temples carved into pink sandstone cliffs, earning its nickname, the "Rose City."

items.name: Nemrut Mountain, Turkey
items.description: The mountain lies 40 km north of Kahta, near Adıyaman. In 62 BCE, King Antiochus I Theos of Commagene built on the mountain top a tomb-sanctuary flanked by huge statues 8–9-metre high of himself, two lions, two eagles and various Greek and Iranian gods, such as Heracles-Artagnes-Ares, Zeus-Oromasdes, and Apollo-Mithras-Helios-Hermes.These statues were once seated, with names of each god inscribed on them.

items.name: Longtail boats at Railay beach,Thailand
items.description: Railay is a small peninsula between the city of Krabi and Ao Nang in Thailand. It is accessible only by boat due to high limestone cliffs cutting off mainland access.

items.name: Aerial view of Maya bay, Phi-Phi Islands, Thailand
items.description: The islands feature beaches and clear water, and the natural environment is protected by national park status. Tourism on the islands exploded since the release of the movie The Beach. Phi Phi Le's Maya Bay is closed to tourists since June 2018 until the ecosystem recovers.

items.name: Batuan temple, Bali, Indonesia
items.description: Batuan Temple is one of the most popular and beautiful village temple which is part of three major temples in a village that is called Tri Kahyangan, and designed with Balinese architecture with split gates, stone guardians, thatched shrines, and detailed carvings.

items.name: Corvin castle, Hunedoara town,Transylvania
items.description: Corvin Castle is a Gothic-Renaissance castle in Hunedoara, Romania. It is one of the largest castles in Europe and figures in a list of the Seven Wonders of Romania.

items.name: Surin Beach, Phuket, Thailand
items.description: Surin Beach is one of Phuket most beautiful bays. The beach itself has clear water and beautiful white sand, and is lined with tall casuarina trees and small Thai style restaurants.

items.name: Agra Fort, India
items.description: Agra Fort is a UNESCO World Heritage site located in Agra, Uttar Pradesh, India. The fort can be more accurately described as a walled city.

items.name: Pura Bratan temple in Bali, Indonesia
items.description: Pura Bratan is a major Hindu Shaivite Shiva temple located near a water body in Bali, Indonesia. The temple complex is located on the shores of Lake Bratan in the mountains near Bedugul.

items.name: Traditional long-tail boats at Railay beach, Thailand
items.description: The easiest way to get to Railay Beach from Krabi Town would be to get to Klong Jilad Pier to get a boat ticket.

items.name: Amur tiger, Russia
items.description: The Amur tiger, formerly known as the Siberian tiger, is one of the largest cats in the world and today, fewer than 500 can be found in the Russian Far East with a small number ranging across the border into China and possibly North Korea.

items.name: Trevi Fountain in Rome, Italy
items.description: The Trevi Fountain is a fountain in the Trevi district in Rome, Italy, designed by Italian architect Nicola Salvi and completed by Giuseppe Pannini and several others. Standing 26.3 metres high and 49.15 metres wide, it is the largest Baroque fountain in the city and one of the most famous fountains in the world.

items.name: Grand Canal in Venice, Italy
items.description: The Grand Canal is a channel in Venice, Italy. It forms one of the major water-traffic corridors in the city. The banks of the Grand Canal are lined with more than 170 buildings, most of which date from the 13th to the 18th century, and demonstrate the welfare and art created by the Republic of Venice.

items.name: Hamburg, Germany
items.description: Hamburg is connected to the North Sea by the Elbe River. It's crossed by hundreds of canals, and also contains large areas of parkland.

items.name: Salzburg, Austria
items.description: Salzburg is an Austrian city on the border of Germany, with views of the Eastern Alps.

items.name: Pietrapertoza, Italy
items.description: Pietrapertosa is a town and comune in the province of Potenza, in the Southern Italian region of Basilicata. In 2019, CNN included Pietrapertosa among "20 of the most beautiful villages in Italy".

items.name: Spanish Steps in Rome, Italy
items.description: The Spanish Steps are a set of steps in Rome, Italy, climbing a steep slope between the Piazza di Spagna at the base and Piazza Trinità dei Monti, dominated by the Trinità dei Monti church at the top.

items.name: The magnificent Great Wall of China
items.description: The Great Wall of China is the collective name of a series of fortification systems generally built across the historical northern borders of China to protect and consolidate territories of Chinese states and empires against various nomadic groups of the steppe and their polities.

items.name: Grand Canal, Venice
items.description: The Grand Canal not only connects most of Venice's top tourist attractions, it is one of its top attractions. Curving in a reverse S through the heart of the city, it is also Venice's Main Street, always busy with traffic that includes everything from gondolas to barges carrying produce to market.

items.name: Pantheon in Rome, Italy
items.description: The Pantheon is a former Roman temple, now a Catholic church, in Rome, Italy, on the site of an earlier temple commissioned by Marcus Agrippa during the reign of Augustus. It was completed by the emperor Hadrian.

items.name: Matera, Italy
items.description: Matera is a city on a rocky outcrop in the region of Basilicata, in southern Italy. It includes the Sassi area, a complex of cave dwellings carved into the mountainside.

items.name: Colorful keel-billed toucan bird
items.description: The keel-billed toucan is a colorful Latin American member of the toucan family. It is the national bird of Belize.

items.name: Zion National Park, Utah
items.description: Zion National Park is a southwest Utah nature preserve distinguished by Zion Canyon’s steep red cliffs.

items.name: Canyonlands National Park, Utah
items.description: Canyonlands National Park in southeastern Utah is known for its dramatic desert landscape carved by the Colorado River.

items.name: Na Pali coast, Kauai
items.description: Nāpali Coast State Wilderness Park lies in the northwest of Kauai Island, Hawaii. It’s known for its towering pali, or sea cliffs, punctuated by narrow valleys, streams and cascading waterfalls.

items.name: Wildlife photography in Namibia
items.description: The African leopard is native to many countries in Africa. It is widely distributed in most of sub-Saharan Africa. Leopards have been recorded in North Africa as well.

items.name: Mountain lake Lacul Rosu, Romania
items.description: Red Lake is a natural dam lake formed following the collapse of a slope due to the earthquake of January 23, 1838. The surroundings of the lake have a pleasant microclimate, particularly beneficial for the treatment of physical and mental exhaustion, insomnia, neurasthenia.

items.name: Unique rock formation in the Arizona desert, USA
items.description: In the United States, most of the Sonoran Desert can be found in the southern third of Arizona, with small areas in southeastern California. It is a subtropical desert and the most complex desert in North America.

items.name: Capo San Marco lighthouse, Italy
items.description: The lighthouse was built in 1924 and consists of a masonry ochre quadrangular tower, 15 metres high, with double balcony and lantern atop a 2-storey keeper's house. The lighthouse, since 1969, was managed by Elisabetta Deriu widow of the lighthouse keeper who died in service in 1967.

items.name: Eibsee lake, Bavarian Alps
items.description: Eibsee is a lake in Bavaria, Germany. It lies at the base of the Zugspitze, Germany's highest mountain.

items.name: Fantastic Selfoss waterfall, Iceland
items.description: A few hundred meters downstream of the Selfoss waterfall, the Dettifoss waterfall is situated, the most powerful waterfall in Europe. Below the falls, the river passes through a gorge which is part of the Jökulsárgljúfur National Park.

items.name: Hvitserkur unique basalt rock, Iceland
items.description: Hvítserkur is a 15 m high basalt stack along the eastern shore of the Vatnsnes peninsula, in northwest Iceland. The rock has two holes at the base, which give it the appearance of a dragon who is drinking.

items.name: Studlagil canyon, Iceland
items.description: Stuðlagil Canyon is found in the plateaus of East Iceland, not far from the black beaches of the Eastfjords. The closest major town is Egilsstaðir, 72 km to the east.

items.name: Lake Federa, Italy
items.description: Lago Federa is possibly one of the most beautiful lakes in the Dolomites. Monte Pelmo is reflecting in the lake.

items.name: Splendid view of famous crater Viti
items.description: Víti is an explosion crater in the Krafla fissure area of North Iceland. It is one of the two most famous Víti craters in Iceland, the other being Víti in Askja. The name of both means’ hell’, in reference to the violence in the past.

items.name: Amazing view of Svartifoss waterfall
items.description: Svartifoss is a waterfall in Skaftafell in Vatnajökull National Park in Iceland, and is one of the most popular sights in the park. It is surrounded by dark lava columns, which gave rise to its name.

items.name: Reynisfjara black sand beach
items.description: Reynisfjara is a world-famous black-sand beach found on the South Coast of Iceland. With its enormous basalt stacks, roaring Atlantic waves and stunning panoramas, Reynisfjara is widely considered to be the most beautiful example of Iceland’s black sand beaches.

items.name: Stokksnes Cape, Iceland
items.description: Stokksnes is a headland on the southeastern Icelandic coast, near Hofn and Hornafjördur. The Iceland Air Defense System uses the station to monitor Iceland's airspace.

items.name: Pinagbuyutan Island, Philippines
items.description: What makes Pinagbuyutan island special is the colorful and thriving underwater ecosystem beneath its glass-like waters. With patches of cogon grass, a white sand shoreline, a coconut grove, and limestone formations, the diverse natural elements on this small island make for interesting photos.

items.name: Maya Bay in Ko Phi Phi Le Island, Thailand
items.description: Maya Bay is a stunningly beautiful bay that's sheltered by 100-metre high cliffs on three sides. Inside the bay there are several beaches, most are small and some only exist at low tide.

items.name: Khao Phing Kan, Thailand
items.description: Khao Phing Kan consists of two forest-covered islands with steep shores. Waters around the island are only few metres deep and are pale-green in colour. The bottom is covered with silt. Khao Phing Kan means 'hills leaning against each other' in Thai, reflecting the connected nature of the islands.

items.name: Saar river, Germany
items.description: The Saar is a river in northeastern France and western Germany. The name Saar stems from the Celtic word sara (streaming water), and the Roman name of the river, saravus.

items.name: Sirindhorn Wararam Phu Prao Temple, Thailand
items.description: This Buddhist temple boasts the main hall with nice artwork that is illuminated at dusk. The main artwork is a ceramic tiles wall which is nice to look at during the day but will look very impressive when illuminated.

items.name: Villa Monastero, Italy
items.description: Villa Monastero is located in Varenna, Province of Lecco, on the shore of Lake Como. The villa lies south of the village, halfway between Varenna and Fiumelatte, and includes a botanical garden, a museum, and a convention center.

items.name: Ban Gioc waterfall
items.description: Ban Gioc is a collective name for two waterfalls on the Quây Sơn River, that straddle the international border between China and Vietnam.

items.name: Skogafoss waterfall, Iceland
items.description: Skógafoss is a waterfall situated on the Skógá River in the south of Iceland at the cliffs of the former coastline.

items.name: The Azores, Portugal
items.description: The Azores, an autonomous region of Portugal, are an archipelago in the mid-Atlantic. The islands are characterized by dramatic landscapes, fishing villages, green pastures and hedgerows of blue hydrangeas.

items.name: Stunning waterfall in Laos
items.description: Laos is full of cascading waterfalls plunging into blue pools. Many of these waterfalls have been developed into tourist attractions.

items.name: Kirkjufellsfoss waterfall
items.description: Kirkjufellsfoss is modest, low lying waterfall which drops 54 feet in two broad steps as its stream makes its final plunge to a lagoon along the shore of the ocean, with the famous mountain Kirkjufell looming above.

items.name: Aerial photo of migrating elephant herd
items.description: The herd is made up of the oldest and largest matriarch who leads her daughters and their offspring. A family can consist of anywhere between 2 and 50 elephants. Occasionally, other non-related females may be included in a herd, but this is rare.

items.name: Mountains at Tikhaya Bay, Sakhalin Island, Russia
items.description: On the east coast of Sakhalin island, Tikhaya Bay lives up to its name, which means “quiet,” and it’s as tranquil as it is strikingly beautiful. Named by the Russian explorer Ivan Fedorovich Kruzenshtern, Tikhaya Bay is not marked on most maps, which helps explain the lack of tourists.

items.name: Paiyu peak
items.description: Morning sunrise over Paiyu peak in Karakoram mountain range of Pakistan

items.name: Vienna Scene
items.description: Evening view of the statue of Archduke Charles on the Heldenplatz in Vienna, Austria.

items.name: Val di Funes, Trentino Alto Adige, Italy
items.description: View of the Santa Magdalena village with The Dolomites in the background.

items.name: Silk Road, Sikkim
items.description: Curvy roads of the Silk Road, an ancient network of trade routes between China and India.

items.name: Waterfalls Landscape
items.description: Sunrise scene on the Selfoss Waterfall in Jokulsargljufur National Park, Iceland.

items.name: Winter Iceland Lanscape
items.description: Winter morning on the road towards the mountains, Iceland.

items.name: Plitvice Lakes National Park, Croatia
items.description: Breathtaking nature view in the Plitvice Lakes National Park, the largest national park in Croatia.

items.name: Avenue of the Baobabs
items.description: Beautiful Baobab trees at sunset at the Avenue of the Baobabs in Menabe, Madagascar.

items.name: Kuang Si Falls
items.description: Waterfalls of the Kuang Si Falls, a three tier waterfall about 29 kilometres in Luang Prabang, Laos.

items.name: Erawan National Park
items.description: Waterfalls at the Erawan National Park, Tenasserim Hills, Kanchanaburi Province, Thailand.

items.name: Hoge Veluwe National Park
items.description: Beautiful autumn forest in the National Park De Hoge Veluwe in, Gelderland, Netherlands.

items.name: Mountain Sunset
items.description: Beautiful sunset at the Monument Valley, USA.

items.name: Tre Cime di Lavaredo
items.description: Views from the clouds of the Italian National Park Tre Cime di Lavaredo in the Sexten Dolomites of northeastern Italy.

items.name: Dry Tortugas National Park
items.description: View of the Dry Tortugas National Park in Monroe County, Florida, United States.

items.name: Maroon Bells
items.description: Reflection of snow capped Maroon Bells, two peaks in the Elk Mountains in Colorado, U.S.

items.name: Oneonta Falls
items.description: Beautiful waterfall and canyon in Oneonta Gorge trail, Oregon, U.S.

items.name: Kelimutu National Park
items.description: Steaming volcanic colourful lakes in Kelimutu craters, Flores, East Nusa Tenggara, Indonesia.

items.name: The Marble Caves
items.description: The Marble Caves of Chile a are part of the General Carrera Lake, located in Patagonia and shared by Argentina and Chile.

items.name: Mexican Natural Pool
items.description: Ik Kil is a well known cenote outside Pisté in the Tinúm Municipality, Yucatán, Mexico.

items.name: Whitehaven Beach
items.description: Beautiful landscape of Whitehaven Beach in the Whitsunday Island, Australia.

items.name: Grand Railway Hotel
items.description: The Fairmont Banff Springs Hotel at night, Alberta, Canada.

items.name: Japanese Cherry Blossoms
items.description: Beautiful cherry blossom tunnel over river in Tokyo, Japan.

items.name: Spring blossoms
items.description: Spring landscape with multicoloured tulips.

items.name: Texas Wildflower
items.description: Bluebonnet and indian paintbrush filed in sunset.

items.name: Reed Flute Cave
items.description: The beautifully illuminated Reed Flute Cave displaying the "Crystal Palace of the Dragon King" formations, Guilin, Guangxi Provine, China.

items.name: Fly Geyser, Nevada
items.description: The Fly Geyser constantly erupts minerals and hot water creating bright colours and terraced pools.

items.name: The Cave
items.description: Magnificent view of the Devetashka cave, Devetaki, Bulgaria.

items.name: Daigo-ji Temple
items.description: Daigo-ji temple, a Shingon Buddhist temple, with autumn foliage leaves in Fushimi-ku, Kyoto, Japan.

items.name: Tian Tan Buddha
items.description: The Big Buddha is the biggest sitting Buddha statue built outdoor. This majestic statue sits atop the peak of Mount Muk Yue, Hong Kong, China.

items.name: Chiang Kai-shek Memorial Hall
items.description: Early morning at the Archway of the Chiang Kai-Shek Memorial Hall, Tapei, Taiwan.

items.name: Scenic Landview
items.description: Landscape of Guilin, Li River and Karst mountains, located near Yangshuo County, Guangxi, China.

items.name: Dugald Stewart Monument
items.description: The Dugald Stewart Monument is an iconic monument over looking the city of Edinburgh, Scotland, built in memory to the Scottish philosopher Dugald Stewart.

items.name: Chocolate Hills, Philippines
items.description: The Chocolate Hills are a geological formation  covered in green grass that turns brown during the dry season, hence the name.

items.name: Yosemite National Park
items.description: Half dome rock that overviews the Yosemite National Park during Sunset, California, United States.

items.name: Lake Louise, Canada
items.description: Located in the Banff National Park, it offers one of the largest ski resorts during winter in North America.

items.name: Mount Bromo
items.description: Bromo volcano at sunrise, the only active crater in the Tengger caldera which contains seven eruptive centres, Tengger Semeru National Park, East Java, Indonesia.

items.name: Denali National Park
items.description: Early morning view of Mount Denali, the tallest peak in continental North America. One of those rare moments when the peak is not covered in clouds.

items.name: Ancient Pyramids
items.description: View of the pyramids from the Giza Plateau, which lies on the edge of the modern city of Cairo, Egypt.

items.name: Sheikh Zayed Grand Mosque
items.description: Abu Dhabi hosts the third largest mosque in the world,the  Sheikh Zayed Grand Mosque, built with the rise of 11 metres above sea level, and 9.5 metres above the street level.

items.name: Tea Plantation hills in Munnar
items.description: Beautiful landscape of green tea plantation hills in Munnar, Kerala, India.

items.name: Mu Cang Chai
items.description: Beautiful terraced rice field in harvest season in sunset in Mu Cang Chai, Vietnam.

items.name: Goreme national park
items.description: Colourful hot air balloons flying over the volcanic mountains in Goreme national park, Cappadocia, Anatolia, Turkey.

items.name: Neuschwanstein Castle
items.description: The Neuschwanstein Castle is one of the most visited castles in Germany located in Bavaria, near the town of Fussen. It was built by King Ludwig II of Bavaria, also known as the “Fairytale King”.
